http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/Man-kills-lover%E2%80%99s-father-in-law-held/article14008748.ece

A 55-year-old man was murdered in West Delhi for inadvertently coming in the way of his daughter-in-law and her lover. “The victim had recently moved to Delhi to stay permanently with his son and daughter-in-law. His presence at home meant that Ansari was unable to meet his lover for more than two weeks,” said Pushpendra Kumar, DCP (West). The suspected murderer has been arrested, five days after the murder. The accused has been identified as 37-year-old Jaseem Ansari, a contractor at a construction site. The deceased man’s son had been working under Ansari for the last three years.The murder came to light last Wednesday when the body of Harkishan (name changed) was found amid thick vegetation between two drains in Nihal Vihar.Subsequent investigations led police to realise that Harkishan’s 28-year-old daughter-in-law Rekha (name changed) was in an extramarital relationship with her husband’s boss, said a senior police officer.Ansari had also gained the trust of Rekha’s family members, including the deceased, by regularly helping the family financially.Under sustained interrogation, Ansari confessed to killing Harkishan, said the police.Ansari had gained the trust of Rekha’s family by helping them financially